cat << EOF
Cinepaint is a motion picture editing tool primarily used for painting and retouching of movies. Its application to feature movie productions includes the movies Scooby-Doo, Harry Potter, and Stuart Little. Cinepaint is the most successful open source tool in feature motion picture work today. Cinepaint runs on Linux and SGI Irix. A Windows version is planned for release in December 2002, and Macintosh native in 2003. Formerly known as filmgimp.
EOF
